# Vanilla JavaScript — Permanent Policy

Shutters is and will remain a **vanilla JavaScript** library. This is not negotiable through the roadmap.

## What “vanilla JS” means here

- **Source:** plain `.js` files only in `src/`, `index.js`, `auto.js`, `demo/` library copies
- **Runtime:** zero `dependencies` in `package.json` — consumers get JS + CSS, nothing else
- **APIs:** browser DOM only (`classList`, `addEventListener`, `CustomEvent`, `querySelector`)
- **Distribution:** ES module + UMD — no transpiler required on the consumer side
- **Dev tooling:** Vite, Vitest, jsdom are **devDependencies only** — never shipped in `dist/`

## Never add (unless the project owner explicitly reverses this policy)

- TypeScript source (`.ts`, `.tsx`) or a TS build step for library code
- React, Vue, Svelte, Angular, Lit, or jQuery — in source or as runtime deps
- Web Component wrapper as the primary API (custom elements / shadow DOM)
- Framework-specific packages or `/react` `/vue` export paths in this repo
- Runtime npm dependencies of any kind

## Allowed

- Hand-written `*.d.ts` for TypeScript **consumers** (optional, no TS source)
- JSDoc in `.js` files
- Copy-paste integration snippets in README (React/Vue mount examples — docs only, not packages)
- CSS for all animation and visual behavior

## Verify before merge

```bash
npm run verify:vanilla
npm test
```
